Incident.Summary: THEFT OF CELLULAR PHONE. VICTIM MET SUSPECT ONLINE. VERY LIMITED INFORMATION ON SUSPECT DURING INITIAL INVESTIGATION.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: SCENE PROCESSING: I, Trooper First Class Scott (#7217) of the Maryland State Police, am equipped with a body-worn camera. My body-worn camera was actively recording during initial investigation. STOLEN PROPERTY: - ONE (1) APPLE iPHONE 13 PRO MAX, BLUE IN COLOR WITH A PINK CASE. APPROXIMATE VALUE: $800.00 TO $1000.00 NEIGHBORHOOD CHECK: The complainant told me she does not know if her neighbors have cameras. She believes the community office for her neighborhood may have a local camera system for the neighborhood. However, considering the time of night that I responded, I assumed the community office would be closed and would need to be contacted during daytime hours. I checked the neighborhood to see if, by chance, the suspect and his vehicle were hiding somewhere in the neighborhood. I did not locate the suspect or his vehicle upon a check of the area. VICTIM: NAME: JENNA LEA STROHMAIER (W/F) DATE OF BIRTH: OCTOBER 18, 1984 ADDRESS: 14 KENNETH DRIVE, RISING SUN, MARYLAND 21911 MD SOUNDEX:MD10273689235 ALTERNATE TELEPHONE NUMBER: (302) 220-9848 NARRATIVE: On May 29, 2023, at approximately 0116 hours, I, Trooper First Class Scott (#7217) of the Maryland State Police, was dispatched to 14 Kenneth Drive, Rising Sun, Maryland 21911 in response to the theft of a cellular phone. I arrived on scene at approximately 0131 hours. Upon arrival, I made contact with Jenna Lea Strohmaier (see VICTIM). Strohmaier told me she met a black male known only as Jerome online. She invited Jerome to hang out with her at her residence the night of this incident. In the process, Jerome asked Strohmaier if he could use her cellular phone (see SCENE PROCESSING). Jerome took Strohmaiers cellular phone outside before she heard his vehicle start. Strohmaier then discovered Jerome fled the area with her cellular phone in his possession. His vehicle was described as a red in color 2020 Hyundai, possibly a Hyundai Sonata. Strohmaier said nothing else of note occurred other than her cellular phone being stolen (i.e. no assault, etc.). Strohmaier had no additional information to help identify Jerome (as in no street address, no telephone number, no last name, no photographs, etc.). The registration plate for his vehicle is also unknown, but Jeromes vehicle is thought to be registered through Virginia. Strohmaier also told me she has epilepsy and relies on her cellular phone for emergency purposes. I advised Strohmaier to have her son call 9-1-1 in the event of an emergency (medical or otherwise) considering she no longer has her own phone. Before clearing, I checked the area for the suspect and/or his vehicle (see NEIGHBORHOOD CHECK). I also provided Strohmaier with a victim/witness brochure, to include the case number, my name/rank/identification number, and the North East Barrack non-emergency line. Strohmaier told me the cellular phone was a gift from a friend and therefore may be insured. I recommended she provide the case number to the insurance company provided the phone is actually insured, and requested she otherwise notify police if the suspect returns. On June 16, 2023, at approximately 1711 hours, I followed up on this case by calling Bay Country Estates (2 Kenneth Drive, Rising Sun, Maryland 21911;(410) 287-2711). I provided the basic details of the case and requested they check their camera footage (if available) for May 29, 2023 around 0100 hours. I request this case be suspended pending the development of leads or a return call from Bay Country Estates regarding footage. All events occurred in Cecil County, Maryland.
